== Japanese ==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana A.png|thumb|right|Katakana letter ア]]
===Etymology===
Simplified form of the kanji [[阿]], taken from the left part of the kanji.

===Katakana character===
'''ア''' (''a'')

# the [a] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese languages
#: The first character of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to あ (''a'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The next katakana character is [[イ]] (''i'').

